@Node "Introduction" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Introduction"

@{b}Introduction@{ub}

  @{fg fill}MUINList.MiamiPanel@{fg text} is a MUI MiamiDx control panel.

  A @{fg fill}MiamiDx control panel@{fg text} lets you control @{fg fill}MiamiDx interfaces@{fg text}
  quickly.

  MiamiDx panel api was written for @{fg fill}ancient sixty years GUI systems,@{fg text}
  like the one in @{fg fill}AmigaOS 3.5/9.@{fg text} It means that is not really usable
  with @{fg fill}MUI@{fg text}.

  Usually, a MiamiDx panel is a simple window, that just asks
  MiamiDx to wait for some signals.

  This can't be applied to MUI.

  @{fg fill}MUINList.MiamiPanel@{fg text} runs as a @{fg fill}stand alone process@{fg text} that comunicates
  with MiamiDx via @{fg fill}Exec messages@{fg text} throght MiamiDx panel api.

  The speed is the same of plain.MiamiPanel, and the look is really
  better.

@EndNode

