@Node "Setup" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Setup"

@{b}Setup@{ub}

  @{fg fill}First@{fg text} of all you must set @{fg fill}MUINList.MiamiPanel@{fg text} as @{fg fill}default panel@{fg text}:
  go to @{fg fill}MiamiDX/Gui/Control panel settings.../Panel module@{fg text} and
  select @{fg fill}MUINList.MiamiPanel@{fg text}.

  In order to make an interface to be in the panel, go to
  @{fg fill}MiamiDx/Interfaces@{fg text}, doubleclick the interface and select
  the checkmark @{fg fill}Control panel@{fg text}.

  Some settings of the panel are available in
  @{fg fill}MiamiDx/GUI/Control panel settings...@{fg text}

  There you may @{fg fill}set@{fg text}:
  - Hotkey
  - Refresh time
  - Show on startup
  - Show transfer rate
  - Show total traffic
  - Show control gadgets
  - Show speed
  - Show online time
  - Show onl/off gadgets

  There are @{fg fill}ignored@{fg text}:
  - Font (set it in MUI Settings)
  - Public screen (set it in MUI Settings)

  The MUINList.MiamiPanel GUI is described @{"here" Link "GUI"}.

  Other settings you should take care of are the @{fg fill}MUI@{fg text} ones:

  - Windows/Fonts/Small for the On/Offline buttons

  - Groups/Frame/Normal for the MiamiDx gadgets group frame
  - Groups/Bacground/Framed for the MiamiDx gadgets group background

  - NListviews/Misc/Misc2/Leading to something like 6 or 8
  - NListviews/ScrollBar/Horiz_Scrollbar to FullAuto
  - NListviews/ScrollBar/Vertical_Scrollbar to FullAuto

  The MUINList.MiamiPanel GUI is described @{"here" Link "GUI"}.

@EndNode

@Node "GUI" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - GUI"

@{b}GUI@{ub}

  MUINList.MiamiPanel opens a very simple interface, whose main
  elements are:

  @{"Menus              " Link "Menus"}
  @{"Interface list     " Link "IFgroup"}
  @{"MiamiDx ctrls group" Link "CGroup"}
  @{"Preferences window " Link "Prefs"}
  About window


@{fg fill}-----------------------------------------------------------------
Note that pressing the Help button in one of the above shows this
guide. @{fg text}

@EndNode

@Node "Menus" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Menus"

@{b}Menus@{ub}

  The MUINList.MiamiPanel menus are:

  o @{fg fill}Project@{fg text}

    - About
      Opens the About window

    - About MUI
      Opens the About MUI window

    - Hide
      The action taken depends on your @{"On iconify" LINK "Prefs"}
      setting: If you choosed Quit, the panel is quit If you choosed
      Iconify, the panel is iconified

    - Quit
      Quit the panel


  o @{fg fill}MiamiDx@{fg text} (See @{"MiamiDx ctrls group" Link "CGroup"})

    - Show
      Open MiamiDx GUI

    - Hide
      Iconify MiamiDx GUI

    - Quit
      Quit Miami


  o @{fg fill}Preferences@{fg text}

    - Edit
      Open the @{"Preferences" Link "Prefs"} window

    - Save
      Save preferences to ENVARC:

    - Use
      Save preferences to ENV:

    - Restore
      Load preferences from ENV:

    - Last saveds
      Load preferences from ENVARC:

    - MUI Settings
      Open MUI Settings window

@EndNode

@Node "IFList" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Interfaces list"

@{b}Interfaces list@{ub}

  It contains the interfaces datas.

  If you @{"choose" LINK "Prefs"} to have the On/Offline gadget you will get one
  button for each interface. Pressing the button will put the
  interface On/Offline.

  The list has also a ContextMenu that may be opened via the right
  mouse button. The menu may be used to put an interface On/Offline.

@EndNode

@Node "CGroup" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - MiamiDx ctrls group"

@{b}MiamiDx ctrls group@{ub}

  If you @{"choosed" LINK "Setup"} to have the MiamiDx ctrls, you will get a Speedbar
  made of 3 buttons. They may be used to control Miami:

  - Show
    Open MiamiDx GUI

  - Hide
    Iconify MiamiDx GUI

  - Quit
    Quit Miami

  See @{"Menus" Link "Menus"}.

@EndNode

@Node "Prefs" "MUINList.MiamiPanel - Preferences window"

@{b}Preferences window@{ub}

  The Prefereces window lets you edit MUINL.MiamiPanel preferences.

  o @{fg fill}Interfaces@{fg text}

    - Traffic format
      . Long
        The traffic is shown in bytes
      . Short
        The traffic is shown in Kb/Mb

    - Grouping
      If selected traffic digits are grouped

    - Rate format
      . Long
        The Rate is shown in bytes
      . Short
        The Rate is shown in Kb/Mb

    - Grouping
      If selected rate digits are grouped

    - Short strings
      If selected, the panel uses short strings (for On/Offline
      gadgets and State)

    - Bold title
      If selected the title of the interfaces list is bold

    - Double click
      If selected, you may doubleclik on an interface to switch its
      state

  o @{fg fill}MiamiDx ctrls@{fg text}

    - Position
      Let you choose where to put the MiamiDx ctrls group

    - Appearance
      The appearance of the buttons bar

    - Borderless
      If selected the buttons are borderless

    - Highlight
      If selected the buttons are rendered in black and with and
      they are coloured when the mouse is over them

    - Raised
      If selected a frame is rendered around borderless buttons
      when the mouse is over them

    - Scaled
      If selected buttons are scaled according to MUI/SpeedBar
      preferences

    - Label pos.
      Let you choose where to put the text for "Icons and text"
      buttons

    - Bar pos.
      Let you choose where to put the buttons bar

    - Underscore
      If selected the control keys of the buttons are active

  o @{fg fill}Options@{fg text}

    - On iconify
      This may sounds strange, but because of a MiamiPanel has no
      iconified state, you may decide to simply quit the panel
      when iconified, or to really iconify it. If iconified with
      an icon, the panel searches for ENVARC:Sys/MiamiPanel.info

    - BWin
      If selected the panel uses BWin.mcc as window class. Note
      that a BWin.mcc window has a very usefull context menu

    - Borders
      If selected the BWin window has borders

  o @{fg fill}Save@{fg text}
    Save preferences and exit

  o @{fg fill}Use@{fg text}
    Use preferences and exit

  o @{fg fill}Apply@{fg text}
    Apply preferences without saving, and exit

  o @{fg fill}Test@{fg text}
    Test preferences without exiting

  o @{fg fill}Cancel@{fg text}
    Exit without saving

@EndNode

